At this point, I don't think that we have enough to go on to come to any conclusions about how PoP will affect the class overall.  We know that player levels are going up and that we're getting new pets, but we need a lot more information before we can tell if this will be a positive or a negative change for the class overall.  <br>
<br>
I agree with Noonie that it would be a great to discuss how the changes will affect us while the expansion is still being finalized, but we're not getting enough info on specifics to allow us to do this.  VI is deliberately keeping things secret to &quot;surprise&quot; us when the expansion is released, so I think we have no choice but to wait for the box to hit the shelves before we can really discuss how PoP affects us overall.<br>
<br>
I think that a lot of the anxiety about this expansion among magicians has to do with what happened with Kunark.  We tend to have bad associations with level cap increases.  About all that we can do at this point, however, is just wait to see what happens and hope that we don't get the shaft again.<br>
<br>
Shanuk Dandiprat<br>
